<span id="freeTextContainer8782216838640095651">Loved the descriptions of the paintings in the Hermitage, this was the highlight of the novel for me. I had a hard time connecting with the characters, not sure if it was the back and forth, but I also felt a lack of emotion. Did like the history conveyed, the German blitz of Leningrad, but I just wanted a little more of something. Alzheimer&apos;s is a terrible disease and I did feel very sorry for the family and Marina, who could still remember the paintings from the past, but had trouble with the </span>
  <span id="freeText8782216838640095651" style="display:none">Loved the descriptions of the paintings in the Hermitage, this was the highlight of the novel for me. I had a hard time connecting with the characters, not sure if it was the back and forth, but I also felt a lack of emotion. Did like the history conveyed, the German blitz of Leningrad, but I just wanted a little more of something. Alzheimer's is a terrible disease and I did feel very sorry for the family and Marina, who could still remember the paintings from the past, but had trouble with the present.</span>
